Red measles (a redundant term) is described as a contagious respiratory disease that is caused by a virus. Children and adults can contact their primary contact care physician if they have not been vaccinated. The MMR vaccine is usually given to babies between 12 and 15 months and again when the child is between 4 and 6 years old. Anyone planning to travel outside of the country is urged by officials to contact their primary physician about vaccinations. - Mod.CP

